2 SENATE BILL 848
1 (II) IMMEDIATELY AFTER A MUNICIPALITY SUBMITS THE
2 INFORMATION REQUIRED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE
3 STATE BOARD SHALL PUBLISH THE INFORMATION ON THE STATE BOARD’S
4 WEBSITE.
5 (2) (I) ON OR BEFORE THE DATE THAT IS 1 WEEK AFTER THE
6 CANDIDATE FILING DEADLINE FOR A MUNICIPAL ELECTION, THE MUNICIPALITY
7 SHALL SUBMIT TO THE STATE BOARD:
8 1. A LIST OF EACH QUALIFIED CANDIDATE FOR EACH
9 OFFICE ON THE MUNICIPAL BALLOT; AND
10 2. INFORMATION ON HOW TO VOTE AND WHERE TO VOTE
11 IN THE MUNICIPAL ELECTION.
12 (II) IMMEDIATELY AFTER A MUNICIPALITY SUBMITS THE
13 INFORMATION REQUIRED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE
14 STATE BOARD SHALL PUBLISH THE INFORMATION ON THE STATE BOARD’S
15 WEBSITE.
16 [(b)] (C) (1) (I) The State Board shall, immediately after a municipality
17 submits its election results, publish the election results on the State Board’s website.
18 [(2)] (II) The election results published under [paragraph (1)]
19 SUBPARAGRAPH (I) of this [subsection] PARAGRAPH shall be organized by election year
20 and the name of the municipality.
21 [(c)] (2) Within 30 days after the results of a municipal election are certified,
22 the municipality shall submit to the State Board an electronic copy of the election results
23 for each office or question voted on at the election, including:
24 [(1)] (I) vote totals for each office or question reported separately by each
25 of the following voting methods, if applicable:
26 [(i)] 1. in–person early voting;
27 [(ii)] 2. mail–in voting or vote–by–mail;
28 [(iii)] 3. provisional voting; and
29 [(iv)] 4. in–person election day voting; and

